<service_mesh_security_guide>
<title>SERVICE MESH SECURITY TESTING</title>

<critical>Service mesh security testing covers Istio/Envoy vulnerabilities, mTLS bypass, authorization policy bypass, sidecar injection attacks, and control plane exploitation.</critical>

<scope>
- Istio security testing
- Envoy proxy exploitation
- mTLS bypass techniques
- Sidecar injection attacks
- Authorization policy bypass
- Traffic interception
- Control plane attacks
</scope>

<mtls_testing>
{% raw %}
# mTLS bypass:
# Check if mTLS enforced:
kubectl get peerauthentication -n namespace

# Test without client cert:
curl http://service.namespace.svc.cluster.local:8080

# Sidecar bypass:
# Direct pod IP access bypasses sidecar
curl http://10.244.1.5:8080
{% endraw %}
</mtls_testing>

<authorization_bypass>
{% raw %}
# Authorization policy testing:
# Check policies:
kubectl get authorizationpolicies -A

# Test unauthorized access:
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer invalid" http://service/admin
{% endraw %}
</authorization_bypass>

<remember>Service mesh security: Test mTLS enforcement, check authorization policies, attempt sidecar bypass via direct pod access, validate control plane security.</remember>
</service_mesh_security_guide>
